post_text:
The Cross Country team will kick off their season tomorrow at home. If you see one of the runners, wish them luck.

In order to ensure the health and safety our participants, we are not allowing spectators at this meet. We do regret any inconveniences this may cause, but are committed to the safety of these kids. We will re-evaluate this for our next home meet on Sept. 12th.

This season will be different because we are all going through different times. However, one thing that will not change is that our team is going to accomplish great things once again this year. We are excited to be able to share those accomplishments with our parents, fans, and community when the time comes!

Good afternoon,

Today we come to you with a message from the Counseling Dept. Students please check your school email. Class schedules were sent out yesterday for you to review. If you have any changes to request please email Mrs. Laurence and she will do her best to get back to you early next week. (ELaurence@thrallisd.org) Understand that with some personnel changes, and the need to make class sizes as small as possible you may not get the dream schedule that you signed up for. Also, there will be no changes after Friday, July 31 since school starts so soon. We appreciate every one's understanding and support.

Be on the lookout for future episodes regarding: Bus and Transportation, Meal Service, Campus & Front Office, Health & Safety, as well as Classroom and Grading procedures just to name a few.

Continue to stay safe,

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MHvlHQhGywc

--
Travis Dube
Principal
Thrall High School
(512) 898-5193
Twitter: @ThrallSecondary
Email: tdube@thrallisd.org

The continued success of the No Tiger in Need program is largely thanks to Sarah Hegstad, who has worked towards the betterment of the project since the first week of school. Sarah could be seen working diligently away at the project during her advisory periods and during lunch, always brainstorming ways to improve it and reach more kids. When donations slowed this year, Sarah decided to create an Amazon Wish List, which quickly garnered success. What began as food donations has expanded to include toiletries and other items as has helped many kids in Thrall. Though we can‚Äôt continue No Tiger in Need and Sarah unfortunately can‚Äôt compete this week at state, we know that it‚Äôll continue as strong as ever in the future, all thanks to Sarah‚Äôs hard work and brilliant ideas.
Way to go, Sarah!
#memberofthemonth #txfccla #fccla

post_text: Celebrating FCCLA Week!
shared_text:
Thrall Fccla
February 13 at 11:07 AM ¬∑

When I was in seventh grade, my older sister, Kylie, was a freshman. Her friends encouraged her to join FCCLA so she could be a part of their Parliamentary Procedure team, and that very first year, she and her team made it to nationals. They flew out to San Diego that summer, and I thought that was the coolest thing in the world, to fly out of the state with a group of my friends. Naturally, when I was a freshman, I joined FCCLA and got a few of my friends together. We formed our own Parliamentary Procedure team and with the help of my sister‚Äôs team and though our own hard word and dedication, we made it to nationals and flew out to Atlanta. Because of my sister‚Äôs support, my friends and I are working on our third year of competition and we‚Äôve been quite successful so far. It‚Äôs thanks to her that my team and I have been able to go to FCCLA competitions and have the wonderful experiences FCCLA brings along with it. #fcclacelebratesfamily #fcclaweek - Kara Sledge, VP of Parliamentary Law

shared_text:
Thrall Fccla
February 11 at 10:51 AM ¬∑

The FCS class, child guidance, showed me that being a teacher means that you are responsible for developing the students learning skills. It helped me find creative ways to teach new material to the students and make sure everyone understands it. Being in a classroom showed me that a teacher has to be a person who can handle all types of personalities, and it taught me how to discipline a child so they can know right from wrong. Child guidance prepared me to be more understanding, patient, attentive, considerate of students needs, helpful, a leader, caring and creative to help children learn and be successful. #myfcclafuture #fcclaweek - Megan Sumbillo
